---
title: Cauliflower Bacon Mac ’n’ Cheese with Cavatappi and Scallions
description: Bacon. Mac ‘n’ cheese. Need we say more? Okay, how about gooey, melty, bouncy, smoky, savory, and cascading with curls of cavatappi? Not convinced? Well, there’s a good amount of calcium-rich cauliflower in there too—roasted, not boiled, to bring out its natural sweetness and give it a crisp-edged tenderness that is sure to please.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5e2860035ccb2412b3567e89-60b95f3f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/cauliflower-bacon-mac-n-cheese-5e2860035ccb2412b3567e89-d9ce9ef9.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/cauliflower-bacon-mac-n-cheese-5e2860035ccb2412b3567e89
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: American
nutrition:
  calories: 890 kcal
  fat: 46 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 83 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 31 g
  sodium: 1280 g
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash
and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from
greens. Toss @cauliflower florets{10} on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle
of @olive oil{2} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until tender,
~{20-25%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (1 1/2 cups
for 4 servings), then drain.

Meanwhile, heat a large, dry #pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4} and cook,
turning occasionally, until just crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat. Transfer
to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Discard all but 1 tsp bacon fat (2 tsp for 4
servings) from pan.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in same pan over medium heat. Add
scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1%minute}. Add @flour{1} and stir constantly
until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}. Slowly whisk in @2% reduced fat milk{6.75},
1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water (1/2 cup for 4), and @chicken stock concentrate{1}.
Increase heat to high and boil until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off
heat; whisk in @Italian cheese blend{1/2}. Season with @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4)
and pepper.

Chop bacon into small pieces. Stir bacon, cavatappi, and cauliflower into pan with
sauce.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water 1 TBSP at a time until pasta
> is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide mac 'n' cheese between plates. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.